title: SFH on complaint case against Tuen Mun Hospital
content_text:
p>
    Following is a transcript of remarks (English portion) made by the Secretary 
    for Food and Health, Dr York Chow, after attending a public function this 
    morning (October 7): Reporter: How will the Hospital Authority follow up on the incident (a 
    complaint involving the death of a 13-year-old boy at Tuen Mun Hospital) as 
    the family blamed the hospital for using surgery as teaching practicing?  Secretary for Food and Health: As far as I know, this is a very complicated 
    operation that requires very sophisticated technique and monitoring during

operation that requires very sophisticated technique and monitoring during 
    the operation, particularly with anaesthetic and post-operation support. As 
    far as the expertise goes, this was done by an international expert together 
    with our local ones. So, I do not think there is any problem with the 
    expertise as required. But whether the procedure itself has gone into any 
    untoward and unnatural event, I do not know because I do not have the report 
    yet. I do not actually have the analysis of the report so far. The Hospital

yet. I do not actually have the analysis of the report so far. The Hospital 
    Authority has engaged external expertise including expert from overseas to 
    assess the operation concerned. I think this will help the family to 
    understand the cause of death of the boy. At the same time, the case would 
    go into the Coroner's Court eventually and the cause of death would be able 
    to be fully investigated. (Please also refer to the
